 MASON HILL ADVISORS Investment Strategy


				
					   Methods of Analysis, Investment Strategies and Risk of Loss A.  Methods of Analysis and Investment Strategies Generally General Investment Philosophy and Process The Funds’ investment objective is to achieve maximum appreciation of capital, consistent with moderate investment risk, through trading and investing in a broad range of domestic, foreign and emerging market securities. There can be no assurances that the Funds will achieve their objectives or that they will not incur losses. The late Benjamin Graham theorized that securities have intrinsic values which can be quantified by diligent analysis. Graham believed that investors should commit their capital only when a security’s market price deviates substantially from its intrinsic worth.  By so doing, the investor would theoretically maximize his opportunity to earn extraordinary returns when the price corrects. Moreover, this strategy has allowed for a margin of safety that has tended to l...Get the Full Report







